            "answer_text": "In The Matrix Trilogy, during the second film Neo is able to disable the Sentinels attacking them by holding his hand out and concentrating. \u201cAha!\u201d said I. \u201cThey appear to be in the \u2018real world\u2019, but I bet they are still in a computer simulation which is why Neo is able to disable them the same way he can disable Agents!\u201d I was expecting that in the third film, it would be revealed that the \u201creal world\u201d was merely another computer simulation to convince humans they had escaped The Matrix. But, instead, Christopher Nolan probably got that idea too and used it in \u201cInception\u201d. ",
